dcterms:creator: Béla Bollobás
Christian Borgs
Jennifer Chayes
Oliver Riordan
dcterms:description: Each input graph is generated as a scale-free network, which is a network whose degree distribution follows a power law. The generation rule involves adding an edge between two existing nodes based on their in-degree and out-degree distributions.
dcterms:title: Scale-free Graph Datasets

dcterms:creator: Réka Albert
Albert-László Barabási
dcterms:description: The input graph is generated by the Barabasi-Albert model, which is another kind of scale-free network. For an input graph with a certain number of edges, additional edges are randomly added based on a Poisson distribution.
dcterms:title: Poisson-random Graph Datasets

dcterms:creator: Alexander D. Kent
dcterms:description: This dataset includes the authentication activities of users on their computers and servers in an enterprise computer network, forming a directed weighted graph where nodes represent computers and directed edges represent authentication actions.
dcterms:title: User Authorization Datasets
